(94, 4, '2014-11-12 19:03:26', 'Important: PayPal Users Must Discontinue Using SSL 3.0 By December 3, 2014', 'To address a vulnerability with the SSL 3.0 security protocol, PayPal and other payment gateways will be disabling SSL 3.0 support. Merchants must upgrade to Transport Layer Service (TLS) by December 3, 2014 to avoid PayPal payment operation failures. Learn more about what you need to do at https://devblog.paypal.com/poodle-ssl-3-0-vulnerability/', 'https://devblog.paypal.com/poodle-ssl-3-0-vulnerability/', 0, 0),
